API.CloneProjectMapItemToViewMap.description: Clones a project map item to the view map.

projectMapNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the navigator item to be cloned. Only navigator items from the project map can be cloned.

parentNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the navigator item below which the new view will be inserted. Only navigator items from the view map are allowed.

createdNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the new navigator item in view map.

API.CreateAttributeFolders.description: Creates attribute folders. To create a folder, its full path has to be provided. The command will create all folders along the path, if they do not exist.

createdNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the new layout navigator item in the layout book.

createdSubsetId.description: The ID of the new subset navigator item in the layout book.

API.CreateViewMapFolder.description: Creates a view folder item at the given position in the navigator tree.

folderParameters.description: This is the name of the new folder.

parentNavigatorItemId.description: The newly created folder will be placed under this parent item. If this parameter is not given the folder will be created as the first item in the View Map list.

previousNavigatorItemId.description: The newly created folder will be placed after this sibling item. If this parameter is not given the folder will be created as the first item under the parent.

API.DeleteAttributeFolders.description: Deletes attribute folders and all the deletable attributes and folders it contains. To delete a folder, its identifier has to be provided.

API.ExecuteAddOnCommand.description: Executes a command registered in an Add-On.

API.Get2DBoundingBoxes.description: Get the 2D bounding box of elements identified by their GUIDs. The bounding box is calculated from the global origin on the floor plan view. The output is the array of the bounding boxes respective to the input GUIDs. Only works for elements detailed in Element Information.

API.Get3DBoundingBoxes.description: Get the 3D bounding box of elements identified by their GUIDs. The bounding box is calculated from the global origin in the 3D view. The output is the array of the bounding boxes respective to the input GUIDs. Only works for elements detailed in Element Information.

API.GetActivePenTables.description: Returns the model view and layout book pen table identifiers.

modelViewPenTableId.description: Model view pen table identifier or an error.

layoutBookPenTableId.description: Layout book pen table identifier or an error.

API.GetAllClassificationSystems.description: Returns the list of available classification systems.

API.GetAllClassificationsInSystem.description: Returns the tree of classifications in the given classification system.

API.GetAllElements.description: Returns the identifier of every element in the current plan.

API.GetAllPropertyGroupIds.description: Returns the identifier of every property group in the current plan. The optional propertyType parameter can be used to filter the results based on the type of the property group (Built-in or User Defined).

API.GetAllPropertyIds.description: Returns the identifier of every property in the current plan. The optional propertyType parameter can be used to filter the results based on the type of the property (Built-in or User Defined).

API.GetAllPropertyIdsOfElements.description: Returns all property identifiers of the given elements. The optional propertyType parameter can be used to filter the results based on the type of the property (Built-in or User Defined).

API.GetAllPropertyNames.description: Returns the human-readable names of available Property definitions for debug and development purposes.

API.GetAttributeFolderStructure.description: Returns the detailed folder structure for the attributes of a given type. If the path is not given, the root folder will be returned

API.GetAttributeFolders.description: Returns the detailed attribute folders identified by their Ids.

API.GetAttributesByType.description: Returns the identifier of every attribute of the given type.

API.GetAttributesIndices.description: Returns the requested indices and guids of attributes.

API.GetBuiltInContainerNavigatorItems.description: Returns the details of the built-in container navigator items identified by their Ids.

API.GetClassificationItemAvailability.description: Returns the ids of property definitions available for a given classification item.

API.GetClassificationSystemIds.description: Returns the list of available classification systems.

API.GetElementsByClassification.description: Returns the identifier of every element with the given classification identifier.

API.GetElementsByType.description: Returns the identifier of every element of the given type on the plan.

API.GetElementsRelatedToZones.description: Returns related elements of the given zones. The related elements will be grouped by type. If multiple zones was given, then the order of the returned list is that of the given zones.

elementTypes.description: If this parameter is given, then only related elements with the requested types will be listed.

API.GetFillAttributes.description: Returns the detailed fill attributes identified by their GUIDs.

API.GetLineAttributes.description: Returns the detailed line attributes identified by their GUIDs.

API.GetNavigatorItemTree.description: Returns the tree of navigator items.

API.GetPenTableAttributes.description: Returns the detailed pen table attributes (including their pens) identified by their GUIDs.

API.GetProductInfo.description: Accesses the version information from the running Archicad.

languageCode.description: The language code of the running Archicad.

API.GetProfileAttributePreview.description: Returns the preview image of each requested profile attribute in a base64 string format.

imageHeight.description: The height of the preview image.

backgroundColor.description: The background color of the preview image.

previewImages.description: The preview images of the profiles.

propertyValuesForElements.description: List of property value lists. The order of the outer list is that of the given elements. The order of the inner lists are that of the given properties.

API.GetPublisherSetNames.description: Returns the names of available publisher sets.

publisherSetNames.description: The names of available publisher sets.

API.GetSectionNavigatorItems.description: Returns the details of the section navigator items identified by their Ids.

API.GetSelectedElements.description: Returns the identifiers of selected elements in the current plan.

onlyEditable.description: Optional parameter that defines whether the selection list should include only the editable elements or all of them. The default value is FALSE

onlySupportedTypes.description: Optional parameter. When it is set to true, only elements with types that are supported by any other JSON API command will be returned.

API.GetStoryNavigatorItems.description: Returns the details of the story navigator items identified by their Ids.

API.GetSurfaceAttributes.description: Returns the detailed surface attributes identified by their GUIDs.

API.GetTypesOfElements.description: Returns the types of the given elements.

API.GetWorksheetNavigatorItems.description: Returns the details of the worksheet navigator items identified by their Ids.

API.GetZoneCategoryAttributes.description: Returns the detailed zone category attributes identified by their GUIDs.

API.IsAddOnCommandAvailable.description: Checks if the command is available or not.

available.description: Returns true if the command is available.

API.IsAlive.description: Checks if the Archicad connection is alive.

isAlive.description: Returns true if the connection is alive.

API.MoveNavigatorItem.description: Moves the given navigator item under the parentNavigatorItemId in the navigator tree. If previousNavigatorItemId is not given then inserts it at the first place under the new parent. If it is given then inserts it after this navigator item.

newName.description: New name of the navigator item.

newId.description: New ID of the navigator item.

API.SetLayoutSettings.description: Sets the parameters (settings) of the given layout.

BoundingBox3DOrError.description: A 3D bounding box or an error.

RGBColor.description: A color model represented via its red, green and blue components.

red.description: The red component of the color model.

green.description: The green component of the color model.

blue.description: The blue component of the color model.

Subset.description: A set of options used to assign IDs to the layouts contained in the subset.

name.description: The name for the layout subset.

includeToIDSequence.description: Defines whether this subset is included in automatic ID assignment or not.

customNumbering.description: Defines whether the IDs are generated automatically or a custom numbering is used.

continueNumbering.description: Defines whether to continue using the ID assignment of the upper levels or not. If 'true', layouts within this subset are going to be assigned IDs as if they were not within this subset, but part of the level above. In this case you only use the Subset as a logical grouping which has no effect on IDs.

useUpperPrefix.description: Defines whether to use the prefix and ID of the upper levels or not. If 'true', layouts in this subset will be assigned IDs based on the previous layout in the layout book structure.

addOwnPrefix.description: Defines whether to add own prefix to the subset or not.

numberingStyle.description: The style of the ID formatting.

startAt.description: The starting value of the numbering.

ownPrefix.description: The custom prefix for the subset.

ElementComponentId.description: The identifier of an element's component.

ElementComponentIdArrayItem.description: An item of a component array.

ElementComponentsOrErrorArray.description: Array of component list or error.
